  <title><media type="image" src="figures/modem-manager-gui-logo.png">GNOME Hello logo</media>Modem Manager GUI manual</title>
  
  <p>
   <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> is a graphical frontend for the ModemManager daemon
   which is able to control specific modem functions.
  </p>
      <p>
       You can use <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> for the following tasks:
      </p>
      <list>
       <item>
        <p>Send and receive SMS messages with messages concatenation</p>
       </item>
       <item>
        <p>Send USSD requests and receive answers in system encoding</p>
       </item>
       <item>
        <p>Get modem and SIM information (device info, operator name, mode, IMEI,
        IMSI/ESN, Signal level)</p>
       </item>
       <item>
        <p>Scan available mobile networks</p>
       </item>
       <item>
        <p>Control data transmission process and set session traffic and time limits</p>
       </item>
      </list>

